text: Priscila da Silva Sena (Olinda, November 13, 1990), better known by her stage name Priscila Senna, is a Brazilian singer and songwriter. She became known nationally for being part of the band Musa, in which she was the lead singer. Its popularity and mass audience is concentrated in the Northeast Region of the country. During her career, she was a member of the band Musa, where she remained for at least 13 years and decided to pursue a solo career in 2012. == References == Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Brazilian singers
